<text id="02-output-contract" title="Research Repository OPS — Output Contract" version="1.0.0" est_tokens="700" depth="essential">
  <summary>A ops artefact comprising: a step list (preconditions, action, actor, artefact, rollback), a wall-clock budget per phase, and a post-run record committed to the agreed evidence folder.</summary>

  <section title="Required fields">
    <list>
      <item>step.precondition (state, alert, ticket, signal)</item>
      <item>step.actor (role + system)</item>
      <item>step.action (verb + object + parameters)</item>
      <item>step.artefact (link / id of produced artefact)</item>
      <item>step.rollback OR step.stop_branch</item>
      <item>phase.budget (wall-clock minutes)</item>
      <item>run-record (start_ts, end_ts, branches, exceptions, links)</item>
    </list>
  </section>

  <section title="Forbidden patterns">
    <antipattern>
      <description>vague actors (&quot;someone notifies&quot;)</description>
      <reason>Vague actors fail under stress.</reason>
    </antipattern>
    <antipattern>
      <description>side-effect steps without rollback or STOP branch</description>
      <reason>Operator gets stuck mid-procedure.</reason>
    </antipattern>
    <antipattern>
      <description>no phase budgets</description>
      <reason>Window-blowing runs go undetected until the second alarm.</reason>
    </antipattern>
    <antipattern>
      <description>missing run-record after execution</description>
      <reason>Without records the runbook cannot improve.</reason>
    </antipattern>
  </section>

  <section title="Self-check checklist">
    <list>
      <item>Every step has precondition + actor + artefact + rollback.</item>
      <item>Each phase carries a wall-clock budget.</item>
      <item>Run record committed after execution.</item>
      <item>Escalation criteria explicit.</item>
      <item>Runbook owner named in header.</item>
    </list>
  </section>
</text>
